The advanced SureFire SFMB-556-1/2-28 muzzle brake, which fits M4 / M16 weapons and variants with 1/2-28 muzzle threads, greatly reduces both recoil impulse and muzzle rise so that the weapon tracks straight back to keep you on target for faster shot-to-shot recovery. All SureFire SOCOM Series muzzle brakes have blind pilot holes at the 3 and 9 o’clock position to enable fine-tuning of recoil characteristics for individual shooting styles or ammunition characteristics. They also have blind pilot holes at the 6 o’clock position to enable indexing the adapter at bottom dead center, and to pin-and-weld on short-barreled rifles. title: For Sale:  Hard to get a hold of Archangel AK stock.
postcontent:
Fits AK/Saiga/RPK receivers.  Is adjustable for length of pull and comb (cheek weld) this is an affordable option for an AR style stock without having to pay $80+ for an adapter and tube before you even buy a stock of your choosing.  I am willing to sell this stock for exactly what I paid for it. My computer messed up and reloaded my order page and ordered 2 of these stocks.  One I will keep to put on my Saiga 308. And the other one i just want what inlaid for it.  The stocks get here tomorrow so I can't take an actual product picture right now.  And when I receive it I will not take it out of the packaging.  I want whoever buys this item to receive a brand new in box and original factory plastic  stock with no possibility of it having been tampered with. I may take a picture of the stock I will be keeping just to show what it looks like on a gun.  By the way with the cheek riser unfolded it makes it look strikingly similar to the FN SCAR or remington ACR stock. Very attractive stock!  I just don't need 2.
For now I will put a few pictures up from the archangel website.
I paid $70 shipped. I won't ask for a penny more. I don't want to profit I'm just hoping to break even. So the price is $70.  I don't really want to haggle but feel free to make an offer. Worst I can say is "no." 
This is a deal for those that can't find them or don't want to wait for shipping I ordered these stocks from archangel manufacturing. If you go to their website you'll notice there is a 4-6 week wait on all orders for items in stock.  And I got the very last 2 they had. So they have to manufacture a new batch of stocks, package and log them, then fill orders in the order they were received. Which I'm sure is more time on top of that. So if you want this stock you can wait 3-5 months or pay the same price and pick it up same day. 
Like I said I'm not trying to profit. Just made a computer error and wanna fix it.

postcontent:
MERWIN HULBERT & CO, THIRD POCKET MODEL DA .38
.38 cal., 5 shot, double action, folding hammer spur.

Merwin Hulbert offered very high quality revolvers which were serious competitors with the Colt, Smith & Wesson, and Remington large frame single actions during this era. Their guns are believed to have been manufactured in a separate section of the Hopkins & Allen plant. Most will have both Merwin Hulbert and Hopkins & Allen markings on the barrel.
Merwin revolvers have a unique twist-open mechanism. The latch on the bottom of the frame is pushed toward the rear, while barrel & cylinder are twisted clockwise and pulled forward. This design was intended to allow selective ejection of empty cases while leaving unfired cartridges in the cylinder.
